text: Thanks for the great video..I watch your videos everyday and as Procurement professional, i have dealt with number of RPA vendors in India too... there's a lot going on India too on the RPA front and this defntly looks the next tech which is picking... my only doubt here not with this company but with RPA in general,  is the lack of entry barriers to this.. I mean if you just check in India there'll be many firms springing up and ready to customize the Invoices and what not which u want to automate.. I dont see it as a moat which one firm might carry & hence have pricing power (though I do agree that once it's sold to a client, the stickyness might remain) ..but again the client might re-engage with you on negotiations and there's always IP which client may retains and scout for a new partner or atleast show you he's scouting for one to keep pricing tight... but anyways, that's my view & I may be wrong... great video nonetheless..thanks
